# Financial Fraud Defender

> **Built for the Meta PyTorch OpenEnv Hackathon вҖ” April 2026**

A production-grade Reinforcement Learning environment where an AI agent
processes a live stream of financial transactions and decides to **APPROVE**,
**BLOCK**, or **VERIFY via OTP** вҖ” exactly like fraud detection systems at
Razorpay, Stripe, and Visa that run **65,000 decisions per second** against
**$32 billion in annual fraud losses**. The asymmetric reward function teaches
agents that requesting OTP verification is often smarter than an outright block,
mirroring the nuanced cost trade-offs real fraud teams face every day.

---

## Why This Is Real-World

| Fact | Source |
|------|--------|
| Visa processes 65,000 tx/sec at peak | Visa Inc. Annual Report |
| Global card fraud losses: $32B/year | Nilson Report 2024 |
| False decline costs banks $118B/year | Javelin Strategy |
| OTP step-up reduces fraud 90%+ with <2% friction | Industry benchmark |

This environment models the exact asymmetry production systems face: **missing
fraud costs 2Г— more than a false block**, and **OTP verification is almost
free** for legitimate customers. An agent that learns this wins.

---

